Privacy Policies
We are committed to protecting your personal information and ensuring transparency in how we collect, use, and safeguard your data. Read our privacy policy to learn more about your rights.
Public Auctions of Texas Privacy Notice
Effective Date:
11/21/2022
At Public Auctions of Texas we prioritize transparency and trust in all our interactions with you—especially when you purchase our products or engage in our services. We believe privacy shouldn’t be complex, so here’s a clear outline of how we collect, use, and share your information. If you’d like more control over your data.
What Information Do We Collect?
We collect basic information like your name, email address, and mailing address to fulfill orders, handle returns, and improve your experience with us. Occasionally, we may collect additional details with your consent to improve our services or introduce you to new offerings.
How Do We Use Your Information?
We use your information for essential business functions, including:
•
Processing and shipping your orders, handling returns, and providing customer service.
•
Communicating with you about our products, promotions, and company updates that may interest you.
•
Improving our website, products, and customer service to better serve you.
•
Protecting against fraud and unlawful activity.
Who Do We Share Your Information With?
In some cases, we share your information with trusted partners to enhance your experience or to perform essential functions. For example:
•
Marketing Services:
We may share your name and mailing address with our marketing partners including Meta Technologies and Google to help us reach you with seasonal updates and promotions.
•
Analytics Providers:
We work with third-party analytics services like Google Analytics to understand website traffic and enhance our digital content.
Cookies and Tracking Technologies
We use cookies to enhance your browsing experience and gather insights about our website traffic. For more details on our use of cookies and to manage your preferences.
Data Retention
We keep your information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined here unless otherwise required by law.
